<p>Kujo Jotaro</p> is a normal, popular <n>Japanese</n> <n>high-schooler</n>, until he thinks that he is possesed by a <n>spirit</n>, and locks himself in <n>prison</n>. <n>After</n> seeing his <n>grandfather</n>, <p>Joseph Joestar</p>, and fighting <p>Joseph</p>'s friend <p>Muhammad Abdul</p>, <p>Jotaro</p> learns that the "<n>Spirit</n>" is actually <n>Star</n> <n>Platinum</n>, his <n>Stand</n>, or fighting energy given a <n>semi-solid</n> form. Later, his mother gains a Stand, and becomes sick. Jotaro learns that it is because the vampire Dio Brando has been revived 100 years after his defeat to Jonathan Joestar, Jotaro's great-great-grandfather. Jotaro decides to join Joseph and Abdul in a trip to Egypt to defeat Dio once and for all. 
